    "what_description": "Spiranthes grandiflora is a terrestrial orchid species belonging to the family Orchidaceae. It is a perennial plant that grows to a height of 30-60 cm, with 2-3 leaves that are lanceolate to elliptical in shape and 10-20 cm long. The inflorescence is a terminal spike, consisting of 5-15 flowers, each measuring 2-3 cm in length, with a white or pale yellow color and a distinctive curved shape. The flowers have 3 sepals and 3 petals, with the lateral sepals and petals being narrower than the middle sepal and petal, respectively. The plant's growth habit is sympodial, with new growth arising from the base of the plant.",
