    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Spiranthes grandiflora are its anti-inflammatory effects, which can be attributed to the presence of flavonoids, particularly kaempferol and quercetin. This plant has been traditionally used to treat various health conditions, including its antiseptic properties that help to prevent the growth of microorganisms, a property that can be linked to the presence of saponins and glycosides. The analgesic and anxiolytic effects of Spiranthes grandiflora have been reported, with bioactive compounds such as volatile oils and phenolic acids contributing to its sedative properties. Its antioxidant properties, which can be attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, help to protect the body from oxidative stress and cell damage. Additionally, Spiranthes grandiflora has been found to exhibit antimicrobial and antiviral activities, which can be linked to the presence of saponins and terpenoids.",
