    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Spiranthes grandiflora are flavonoids, specifically spirantheside, grandiflorin, and kaempferol, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. These flavonoids possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, contributing to the plant's ability to heal wounds and reduce inflammation. The iridoid glycosides, including spirantheside and grandiflorin, have been found to exhibit antimicrobial and antifungal properties, making the plant effective against various infections. The phenolic acids present in Spiranthes grandiflora, such as ferulic acid and sinapic acid, have been reported to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, further supporting the plant's medicinal potential. The combination of these bioactive compounds in Spiranthes grandiflora contributes to its therapeutic effects, including wound healing, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities.",
