    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Spiranthes grandiflora are based on its reported bioactive properties such as antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. A tincture can be prepared by extracting the plant's roots and flowers in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, which can be used to treat conditions like respiratory issues and skin irritations due to its antimicrobial properties. A tea or infusion can be prepared by steeping the plant's roots and flowers in hot water to treat conditions like fever and digestive issues. A decoction of the plant's roots and flowers can be used to treat conditions like menstrual issues and menopausal symptoms due to its reported estrogenic properties. A salve can be prepared by infusing the plant's roots and flowers in a carrier oil like coconut oil to treat skin conditions like wounds and eczema.",
